🧠 Bringing it back to you

Humans lean hard on vision + language. AI adds another “wand”—a way to generate and shape signals. The trick is:

Use the tool, but keep your own calibration.

* Know what channel you’re in (visual, textual, social cue).
* Cross-check with another channel when it matters (a second source, a person, the physical world).
* Notice when something is trying to push your behavior (like “$$$” cues) and decide if you want that.

